$ screen.availWidth - screen.availHeight - screen.availLeft - screen.availTop

The values of `screen.availWidth`, `screen.availHeight`, `screen.availLeft` and `screen.availTop` report the boundaries within which a
→ development/web/browser[browser] window can be placed.

`screen.availWidth` and especially `screen.availHeight` might be smaller than
→ development/web/browser/object-model/screen/width-height[`screen.width` and `screen.height`] because, for example, of the
→ Windows/Appearance/Taskbar[Windows taskbar].

sa:

  → development/web/js-html/coordinates
